-- Owens-Illinois Jumps Most in Four Months on Earnings Outlook
-- B y   T h o m a s   B l a c k
-- 2012-04-11T20:24:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/owens-illinois-jumps-most-in-almost-3-years-on-profit-correct-.html
Owens-Illinois Inc. (OI)  rose the most
in more than four months after the glass-bottle maker said it
may report a 35 percent increase in first-quarter earnings per
share, compared with a year earlier, on higher prices and lower
costs.  Shares advanced 6.9 percent to $23.52 at the close in New
York, the biggest gain since Nov. 30. The stock has gained 21
percent this year.  The Perrysburg, Ohio-based company said in a statement
yesterday it plans to hold an earnings conference call on April
26.  To contact the reporter on this story:
